## 1. System Overview

### What is this system?

The Promotion Engine is a **dynamic, rule-based discount calculation system** built for a ticketing platform. It allows administrators to create and manage promotions and system discounts that are automatically compiled into **Drools Rule Language (DRL)** files and executed at cart checkout time.

### Core Problems It Solves

```
Without this system:
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Discount logic is hardcoded in application code
  Changing a discount requires code change + deployment
  No audit trail of what discount was applied and why
  No way to stack or combine multiple discounts safely
  No rule versioning or rollback capability

With this system:
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────���──
  Admin creates promotions via REST API → auto-compiled to DRL
  Discount rules change without any deployment
  Full audit log of every apply request
  Stackable/non-stackable rules enforced automatically
  Every rule change versioned and rollback supported
```

