### Why `@ElementCollection` for ticket tables?

```
Promotions can apply to specific ticket titles with:
  - Different quantities per title
  - "Apply to ALL tickets of this title" flag

These are variable-length key-value structures
→ Cannot be stored in single columns
→ JPA @ElementCollection creates separate child tables
→ Automatically managed by Hibernate (insert/delete with parent)

promotion_ticket_titles:
  promotion_id | ticket_title
  1            | Adult
  1            | Youth
  1            | Child

promotion_ticket_quantities:
  promotion_id | ticket_title | quantity
  1            | Adult        | 2
  1            | Youth        | 0
  1            | Child        | 0

promotion_ticket_apply_all:
  promotion_id | ticket_title | apply_all
  1            | Adult        | false
  1            | Youth        | true
  1            | Child        | false

IMPORTANT: These tables only populate when applyFullCart = false
           When applyFullCart = true → full cart discount, no ticket logic
```

