```

### RuleDefinition Entity

```
WHY this table exists:
  DRL (Drools Rule Language) content is stored in DB
  On app startup → loaded from DB → compiled into KieContainer
  On promotion publish → new DRL generated → saved → KieContainer reloaded
  This means rules can change WITHOUT restarting the application

Fields:
  ruleName    → unique e.g. "PROMO_SAVE10", "SYSDISCOUNT_LOYALTY_REWARD"
  ruleType    → "PROMOTION" or "SYSTEM_DISCOUNT"
  referenceId → FK to promotion.id or system_discount.id
  drlContent  → full DRL text stored as CLOB/TEXT
  version     → increments on every change
  active      → false = rule excluded from KieContainer
  createdBy   → who created/last updated
```

### RuleHistory Entity

```
WHY this table exists:
  Every time a rule changes, old version saved here
  Enables rollback to any previous version
  Full audit trail of DRL content changes

Fields:
  ruleName    → which rule
  version     → which version
  drlContent  → exact DRL at that version
  action      → CREATED, UPDATED, DEACTIVATED, ROLLBACK_TO_V1 etc.
  changedBy   → who made the change
  changedAt   → when
```

