### DroolsRuleService

```
Responsibilities:
  generatePromotionRule()      → builds DRL from Promotion entity → saves to DB
  generateSystemDiscountRule() → builds DRL from SystemDiscount entity → saves to DB
  deactivateRule()             → marks rule inactive → triggers reload
  rollbackRule()               → copies old DRL version to current → triggers reload
  buildPromotionDRL()          → DRL generation logic for promotions
  buildSystemDiscountDRL()     → DRL generation logic for system discounts

Why DRL is Generated Dynamically:
  Every promotion has different conditions (dates, user type, channel, tickets)
  Hardcoding these would require redeployment per change
  Dynamic DRL = zero-deployment rule changes

Circular Dependency Solution:
  DroolsRuleService needs DroolsEngineService (for reloadRules)
  DroolsEngineService needs DroolsRuleService (for rule content)
  SOLVED by: ApplicationContext.getBean() lazy lookup
  DroolsRuleService does NOT inject DroolsEngineService directly
  It calls applicationContext.getBean(DroolsEngineService.class)
  only when reloadRules() needs to be called
```

### DroolsEngineService

```
Responsibilities:
  init()              → @PostConstruct — load rules from DB on startup
  reloadRules()       → rebuild KieContainer from DB rule_definitions
  buildEmptyContainer()→ empty KieContainer when no rules exist yet
  applyRules()        → main entry point for /api/engine/apply
  validatePromoCodes()→ batch validate all promo codes
  validateDateAndUsage()→ date window + usage limit checks
  fireRules()         → create KieSession → insert facts → fireAllRules
  incrementUsage()    → increment promo usage count in DB
  saveAuditLogAsync() → @Async audit log save

KieContainer Lifecycle:
  Created:  on startup + on every rule change
  Held:     as AtomicReference<KieContainer> (thread-safe)
  Reloaded: on every promotion/discount publish or update
  Old one:  disposed safely after waiting for active sessions
  WHY AtomicReference: allows swap without locking read path

KieSession Lifecycle:
  Created:  new KieSession per apply request (from KieContainer)
  Used:     insert Cart + insert DiscountResult → fireAllRules()
  Disposed: ALWAYS in finally block — memory leak if not disposed
  WHY new per request: KieSession is stateful — cannot be shared
```

