## 8. Drools Rule Engine

### How DRL is Generated

```
Promotion with these settings:
  promoCode    = "MUSEUM20"
  discountType = PERCENTAGE
  amount       = 20
  applyFullCart= false
  ticketTitles = [Adult, Youth]
  ticketQty    = {Adult:2, Youth:0}
  applyAll     = {Adult:false, Youth:true}
  stackable    = true
  priority     = 3 → salience 60

Generates this DRL:
─────────────���─────────────────────────────────────
rule "PROMO_MUSEUM20"
    salience 60
    no-loop true
    when
        $result : DiscountResult(
            promoStackLocked == false,
            isRuleAlreadyFired("PROMO_MUSEUM20") == false
        )
        $cart : Cart(
            hasPromoCode("MUSEUM20") == true,
            currentDateTime >= LocalDateTime.of(2026,1,1,0,0,0),
            currentDateTime <= LocalDateTime.of(2026,12,31,23,59,59)
        )
    then
        double totalDiscount = 0.0;
        // Adult: qty=2
        double base_Adult = $cart.getTicketTitleTotalForQty("Adult", 2);
        totalDiscount += base_Adult * 20.0 / 100.0;
        // Youth: applyAll=true
        double base_Youth = $cart.getTicketTitleTotal("Youth");
        totalDiscount += base_Youth * 20.0 / 100.0;
        $result.addPromoDiscount("PROMO_MUSEUM20",
            "20% off Museum tickets!", totalDiscount);
        update($result);
end
───────────────────────────────────────────────────
```

### Why `no-loop true`

```
Without no-loop:
  THEN block calls update($result)
  update() tells Drools: "DiscountResult changed"
  Drools re-evaluates ALL rules including this one
  If WHEN still matches → rule fires again → infinite loop → OOM

With no-loop true:
  Rule will not re-activate itself due to its own update()
  Prevents same rule firing twice in same session
```

### Why `isRuleAlreadyFired()` check

```
no-loop prevents self-re-activation
BUT another rule's update() can still re-activate this rule

Solution: track fired rules in DiscountResult.firedRuleNames Set
isRuleAlreadyFired("PROMO_MUSEUM20") == false in WHEN block
→ Once rule fires → firedRuleNames.add(ruleName) in addPromoDiscount()
→ Next evaluation: isRuleAlreadyFired() returns true
→ WHEN condition fails → rule does NOT fire again
→ Infinite loop permanently impossible
```

### Why `salience` (Priority)

```
Drools fires rules in salience order (highest first)
Promotions priority 1 → salience 100 (fires first)
Promotions priority 5 → salience 20  (fires last)
System discounts have direct salience value (80, 90 etc.)

WHY ORDER MATTERS:
  Non-stackable promo sets promoStackLocked = true
  If it fires FIRST → all lower-priority promos blocked
  If it fires LAST  → other promos already applied
  Admin controls this via priority field
```

### `update($result)` — Why Needed

```
Drools working memory is read at start of each rule evaluation
If DiscountResult changes (new discount added, lock set)
other rules need to see the updated state

update($result) tells Drools:
"DiscountResult has changed — re-evaluate rules that pattern-match it"

This enables:
  Non-stackable promo fires → sets promoStackLocked=true → update()
  Other promo rules re-evaluate → see promoStackLocked=true → skip
```

