## 10. Promotion Features

### Redemption Methods

```
PROMO_CODE:
  Customer enters code at checkout
  DRL WHEN checks: hasPromoCode("SAVE10") == true
  Validation: code exists, active, not expired, within limits

AUTOMATIC:
  No code needed — rule fires automatically
  DRL WHEN checks: cartTotal > 0 (and other conditions)
  Used for auto-applied promotional discounts
```

### Discount Scope

```
applyFullCart = true:
  Discount applied to total cart value
  ticket tables (titles/quantities/applyAll) are EMPTY
  DRL uses: $cart.getCartTotal()

applyFullCart = false + category set:
  Discount applied to items in that category only
  DRL uses: $cart.getCategoryTotal("Museum Admission")

applyFullCart = false + ticketTitles set:
  Ticket-level discount — most granular
  ticket tables populated in DB
  DRL uses per-title logic:
    applyAll=true  → $cart.getTicketTitleTotal("Adult")
    applyAll=false → $cart.getTicketTitleTotalForQty("Adult", 2)
```

### Stackable Logic

```
stackable = true:
  Can combine with other stackable promos
  promoStackLocked stays false
  Multiple stackable promos can all apply

stackable = false:
  Cannot combine with ANY other promo
  WHEN block checks: promoStackLocked == false
  THEN block sets: $result.setPromoStackLocked(true)
  update($result) → other promo rules re-evaluate
  → they see promoStackLocked=true → they skip

Validation (before Drools):
  If 2+ promos selected AND any is non-stackable → 400 error
  "Promo [FLAT30] is not stackable. Please select it alone."
```

### Usage Limits

```
usageLimit (global):
  Total times this promo can be used by ALL customers
  Checked before fireAllRules() via DB query
  SUM(usage_count) WHERE promo_code = ?

maxUsagePerCustomer:
  Max times ONE customer can use this promo
  Checked per customer via promo_usage table
  After apply: incrementUsage() increments count
```

