## 11. System Discount Features

### Auto-Application

```
System discounts fire automatically — no customer action
Drools applies them based on:
  userType match  (MEMBER, NON_MEMBER, ALL_USERS)
  date window     (startDate/endDate)
  nonStackableLocked state
  stackGroup not already fired
```

### Manager Approval

```
managerApprovalRequired = true:
  Discount applies normally in calculation
  Response has: "managerApprovalRequired": true
  POS system shows alert to operator
  Manager must physically approve before completing transaction
  Used for large exclusive discounts (e.g. 20% seasonal sale)
```

### Stack Groups

```
stackGroup = "EXCLUSIVE_SALE_GROUP":
  Only ONE discount from this group can apply per cart
  DRL WHEN checks: isStackGroupAlreadyFired("EXCLUSIVE_SALE_GROUP") == false
  DRL THEN calls: $result.markStackGroupFired("EXCLUSIVE_SALE_GROUP")
  → Other discounts in same group see group already fired → skip

WHY:
  Prevent two exclusive sale discounts stacking
  e.g. Summer Sale + Winter Sale should not both apply
```

### Non-Stackable System Discounts

```
stackable = false:
  Sets nonStackableLocked = true after firing
  Other system discounts check: nonStackableLocked == false
  → They skip if locked

Different from promoStackLocked:
  promoStackLocked   → controls PROMOTION stacking
  nonStackableLocked → controls SYSTEM DISCOUNT stacking
  These are independent — a non-stackable system discount
  does not block promotions from applying
```

