## 14. Rule Versioning & Rollback

### How Versioning Works

```
Every rule change creates a history record:

Action         | What happens
───────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────
CREATED        │ First time rule generated (version 1)
UPDATED        │ Promo/discount changed (version N+1)
DEACTIVATED    │ Status set to INACTIVE
ROLLBACK_TO_V2 │ Rolled back to version 2 (new version created)

rule_history stores EVERY version's DRL content
This means you can always restore any past state
```

### Rollback Process

```
POST /api/engine/rules/PROMO_MUSEUM20/rollback/1

1. Find history record for PROMO_MUSEUM20 version 1
2. Find current active rule for PROMO_MUSEUM20
3. Save current version to history as "ROLLED_BACK"
4. Set current rule's drlContent = history version 1's DRL
5. Increment version number
6. Save history entry with action "ROLLBACK_TO_V1"
7. reloadRules() → new KieContainer with restored DRL
```

