## 15. Audit Logging

### What Is Logged

```
Every call to POST /api/engine/apply creates a record in
discount_audit_log with:

  customerId          → who made the request
  promoCodes          → comma-separated codes submitted
  originalTotal       → cart total before discount
  totalDiscount       → total amount discounted
  finalTotal          → amount customer pays
  managerApproval     → was approval needed
  rulesFired          → count of discounts applied
  appliedDiscountsJson→ full JSON of all applied discounts
  appliedAt           → timestamp
```

### Why @Async

```
Saving audit log should NOT delay the customer's response
The customer gets their discount result immediately
Audit log is saved in a background thread (@Async)

If audit save fails: logged as ERROR, response unaffected
Customer never sees audit log save failures
```

