## 17. Performance Optimizations

### Batch DB Queries

```
BEFORE: N promo codes = N separate DB calls (sequential)
AFTER:  N promo codes = 1 batch DB call (IN clause)

findByPromoCodeInAndActiveTrue(List<String>)
→ SELECT * FROM promotion WHERE promo_code IN (?,?) AND active=true

findByPromoCodeInAndCustomerId(List<String>, String)
→ SELECT * FROM promo_usage WHERE promo_code IN (?,?) AND customer_id=?

getTotalUsageByPromoCodeIn(List<String>)
→ SELECT promo_code, SUM(usage_count) FROM promo_usage
  WHERE promo_code IN (?,?) GROUP BY promo_code
```

### Config Cache

```
BEFORE: DB hit on every apply request for MAX_PROMOS_PER_CART
AFTER:  In-memory ConcurrentHashMap cache
        DB hit only once (first request) + on admin update
```

### ReadWriteLock for Rule Reload

```
BEFORE: synchronized reloadRules()
        ALL concurrent apply requests blocked during reload

AFTER:  ReadWriteLock
        Read lock:  many apply requests run CONCURRENTLY
        Write lock: only reloadRules() takes it (brief)
        Apply requests never blocked by each other
```

### @Async Audit Log

```
Audit log save happens in background thread
Customer gets response IMMEDIATELY after fireAllRules()
No waiting for DB write of audit data
```

### KieContainer as Singleton

```
KieContainer is expensive to build (DRL compilation)
Built ONCE and held as AtomicReference
Replaced atomically only when rules change
All apply requests share the same KieContainer
Old container disposed safely after active sessions drain
```

